metadata.name: The Antimatter Inscriptions
metadata.description:
The Antimatter Inscriptions is a collection on Ethereum that is given to the first direct purchasers of the 5 Ordinal pieces inscribed on Bitcoin.

For more information, visit antimatter.nullish.org.


Collection Description:

Antimatter features a large array of vibrating squares and circles that pulse in an imperfect synchronicity. The effect is both calming and dizzying, as the viewer is drawn into a hypnotic world of rhythm and movement.

A fully on-chain, hand-typed generative art project that explores the abstract concept of antimatter through visual chaos, forever etched on the Bitcoin blockchain as Ordinals.
